description: This file defines a template interface 'IIteratorType' for iterating over elements, including methods for traversal, validation, and accessing the current element. It is used within the WPEFramework's RPC namespace to facilitate iteration over collections with a specified element type.

classes.name: IIteratorType
classes.description: A template interface for iterator-like behavior over elements, with methods for moving through, validating, and accessing items in a collection.

methods.name: Next
methods.description: Advances the iterator to the next element, returning true if successful.

methods.name: Previous
methods.description: Moves the iterator to the previous element, returning true if successful.

methods.name: Reset
methods.description: Resets the iterator position to the specified index.

methods.name: IsValid
methods.description: Checks whether the current position of the iterator is valid.

methods.name: Count
methods.description: Returns the total number of elements in the collection.

methods.name: Current
methods.description: Returns the element at the current iterator position.
